This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on coreference resolution, which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) and Relational Graph Convolutional Network (R-GCN), which fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training and optimizing models, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses syntactic information and mentions the use of convolutional networks, which can be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
